What:		/sys/kernel/vas
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		Kernel interface for first class virtual address spaces.

		The /sys/kernel/vas directory contains subdirectories for each
		first class virtual address space that is currently known to the
		kernel.

What:		/sys/kernel/vas/<vas>
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		The directories for each first class virtual address space
		contain various files that can be used to collect additional
		information about it.

What:		/sys/kernel/vas/<vas>/name
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		A read-only attribute that can be used to get the user-defined
		name of the corresponding first class virtual address space.

What:		/sys/kernel/vas/<vas>/mode
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		A read-only attribute that can be used to get the access
		permissions of the corresponding first class virtual address
		space.

What:		/sys/kernel/vas/<vas>/user
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		A read-only attribute that can be used to get the owning user of
		the corresponding first class virtual address space.

What:		/sys/kernel/vas/<vas>/group
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		A read-only attribute that can be used to get the owning group
		of the corresponding first class virtual address space.
